{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Correction\nOriginal framing ('no configurable source target') was WRONG. The completion-verification target IS configurable:\n - rebar verify-completion --ref <branch|tag|SHA> (default origin/main; also via REBAR_GATE_REF env and [snapshot].ref config; pass --ref HEAD for a stacked change / feature branch).\n - The close-gate precheck (_completion_precheck, transition_close.py:280) verifies source='attested', ref='HEAD', fetch=False — i.e. it verifies the current worktree HEAD's tree. So the target IS controllable by checking out the commit whose tree you want verified as HEAD before rebar transition <id> in_progress closed (e.g. checkout a stacked story's own commit so its scope AC is evaluated against just that story's tree, not the cumulative tip).\n\n## The actual defect: discoverability\nThe mechanism is not discoverable from the CLOSE workflow:\n - rebar transition <id> <cur> closed exposes NO --ref/--source flag and its --help says nothing about targeting a specific code state; the ref='HEAD' behaviour and the verify-completion --ref / REBAR_GATE_REF / [snapshot].ref levers are only documented on the standalone verify-completion command.\n - Result: closing a STACKED epic (bbf1: ef33<-ce4d<-94f9<-6673<-dfb9), I closed all stories against the cumulative main tip and hit false-negatives on per-story scope ACs ('no core module modified by this story — git diff'), because later stories' changes are present at the tip and the verifier can't run git. I worked around it with manual operator-attestation comments instead of targeting each story's own commit — because I did not discover the configurability.\n\n## Proposed fix (docs + surfacing)\n - Document, in the close/gate docs (docs/plan-review-gate.md and the transition help), how to target a specific code state at close: check out the target commit as HEAD before close (the ref='HEAD' contract), and/or run verify-completion --ref <commit> first; note the REBAR_GATE_REF / [snapshot].ref levers apply.\n - Surface it on the close path itself: add a --ref (and/or --source) passthrough to rebar transition ... closed that forwards to _completion_precheck, so a stacked-epic closer can target a story's own commit without checking out or hand-writing evidence comments.\n - Add the stacked-landing close recipe to the epic-execution / rebar-implement guidance.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The transition-close help and docs/plan-review-gate.md document how the close-time completion target is chosen (ref=HEAD) and how to target a specific commit (checkout and/or a forwarded --ref), including the stacked-epic recipe.\n- [ ] rebar transition <id> closed accepts a way to target the ticket's own commit (a forwarded --ref/--source, or a documented checkout pattern) such that a correctly-scoped stacked-epic story closes WITHOUT a manual operator-attestation comment (regression test).\n- [ ] make lint && make typecheck && make test green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784771253795563001,"uuid":"dcfa7787-a6e2-41ef-8654-437dbd165a54"}